				<div class="row sub-section bg-blue">
					<div class="container">
						<div class="col-xs-12">
							<h2>outcome&nbsp;</h2>
							<div class="h2-wrap">
								<div class="h2-helper">&nbsp;</div>
							</div>
							<p>I analysed the results from the usability testing in light of <i>Nielsen's 5 qualities of usability</i>. My observations have been listed below.</p>
							<span class="outcomes"><strong>learnability - </strong>Make the menu items on the navigation bar more descriptive</span>
							<span class="outcomes"><strong>efficiency - </strong>The checkout process is simple and seamless</span>
							<span class="outcomes"><strong>memorability - </strong>Add an option to review past purchases in the Account information section of the site</span>
							<span class="outcomes"><strong>error management - </strong>Positive feedback ont he ability to request a toy if a search shows no results</span>
							<span class="outcomes"><strong>satisfaction - </strong>The post-purchase message is positive and encourages users to continue browsing the site</span>
						</div>
					</div>
